733303f-a.title: Street scenes - Wishing tree.
733303f-a.text:
Street Scenes - Manhatten: The wishing tree at the corner
of Aest 132nd Street and Seventh Avenue, Harlem. This is
considered a good luck charm fbr actors in quest of bookings.
It was dedicated on May 23, 1939 in the Savoy Ballroom at the
New York Worlds Fair by Bill Robinson the negro dancer. An
article on its disappearance from there was published in the
New York Post of June 13, 1939.
1936
W. P. A., photo
Federal Writers Project
